Comparison of the same app (Sierpinski triangle) on $mol and other frameworks.

Sources

- $mol implementation
- Others

Results

- React Stack: Everything slows down a lot.

- React Fiber: Smooth animation, quick response to hover, but the content is rarely updated.

- Glimmer: Smooth animation, but a strong reaction delay when hovering

- Glimmer AsyncDom: Incorrect first rendering, smooth animation, but a strong reaction delay when hovering

- $mol: Everything smooth and instant.

Notice

- This test mostly checks the effectiveness of data-flow, rather than rendering.

862√ó485, 19.7 KB
Comparison of code changelog on $mol, Vue and Vanilla.

Cases

- Initial - first show of loaded file with ~1000 lines (10_000 in $mol version).
- Expand - time to expand already loaded but collapsed file with ~1000 lines.
- Reflow - time to full reflow on window resize with expanded file with ~1000 lines (10_000 in $mol version).

Results

 Initial Expand Reflow
$mol 380 ms 120 ms 20 ms
Vue 2080 ms 1200 ms 390 ms
Vanilla 700 ms 460 ms 700 ms

- $mol version opens 2x - 5x faster despite the larger amount of data.
- $mol version interacts 4x - 10x faster
- $mol version reflow time independent of data size.

Notice

- $mol implementation instantly shows changelog with 10K lines while others don't show large files until click.
- $mol version has less functionality, but it doesn't greatly affect the results with large files rendering.
- $mol version supports line wrapping while others show horizontal scroll.
